39;s duration, unreal between cycles =\r\nand is conditionally real when looking across cycles. Freedom is interactin=\r\ng with the world with no attachment from inside the world; realizing the ab=\r\nsolute unreality of the world from outside; and is both of these when looki=\r\nng across cycles.\n\nFrom all points of view, the thinning of the accumulated=\r\n conditioning (vAsanA-tAnavam) is the key.\n\nsasneham,\n=C2=A0\n=C2=A0 =C2=A0a=\r\njit\n=C2=A0\n=C2=A0\n\n\n\nOn Mon, Jul 30, 2012 at 12:04 PM, rajarshi nandy &lt;raja=\r\nrshi14@...&gt; wrote:\n\n\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;Dear Ajit,\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;&lt;Even if the play goes on=\r\n, \ndifferent actors may play the part.&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;Interesting. This did not cros=\r\ns my mind. Variety is the spice of life!\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;&lt;I\n am curious -- do you beli=\r\neve that the universe is maya (the way it it \ncommonly portrayed by advaiti=\r\nns), or do you believe that it is &quot;real&quot; \n(the way it is commonly portrayed=\r\n by dvaitins)? Or perhaps something \ndifferent altogether?&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;I believe th=\r\nat &quot;Maya&quot; means a sort of limited perception due lack of complete informati=\r\non. It exists not just in the physical universe, but even in other non-phys=\r\nical states, though the degree maybe different. Is the average waking consc=\r\niousness real? Yes. Are higher/different states of awareness real? Yes. \n&gt;\n=\r\n&gt;Everything, from the physical world to non-physical realms exist and is an=\r\n extension of the Supreme. Maya is nothing more than whatever obstructs an =\r\nindividual&#39;s mind from realizing that inherent unity. From an individual (h=\r\numan entity) perspective, the point of maximum stillness is the Purusha, wh=\r\nat is called atmah/soul, and everything else, from points of lesser stillne=\r\nss to the external objective reality is Shakti. Extending this principle to=\r\n the Universe, the purely transcendental non-changing, non-negotiable reali=\r\nty can be called the &quot;atmah&quot; while everything else, semi-transcendental to =\r\nthe objective\n reality all around is Shakti. Thus in short, using scriptura=\r\nl terms, Nirguna Brahman is the state of mind of God, while the Universe(s)=\r\n/various realm(s) is the body of God. Both are irrevocable linked for all p=\r\nractical purposes.=C2=A0 Maya is whatever inhibits an individual cell (a hu=\r\nman being or animal or plant or anything) in the body of the God - that is =\r\nUniverse(s) - from realizing the greater picture. \n&gt;\n&gt;Am I making sense? -:=\r\n)\n&gt;\n&gt;-Regards\n&gt;=C2=A0Rajarshi\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabu=\r\nddhayah |\n&gt;param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;_______=\r\n_________________________\n&gt;\n&gt;From: Ajit Krishnan &lt;ajit.krishnan@...&gt;\n=\r\n&gt;To: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com \n&gt;Sent: Monday, 30 July 2012 5:50 PM\n&gt;Sub=\r\nject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Moksha\n&gt; \n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0 \n&gt;Dear Rajarshi,\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt; When=\r\never a ring falls here,=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; a Hanumana follows it and we know=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n it is time for a Rama to leave his body.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;Even if the play goe=\r\ns on, different actors may play the part. Every station within this realm c=\r\nan be attained by &quot;human&quot; effort. It is not simply destined to happen. The =\r\nManus, Indras, and *all other beings* are simply roles played by some being=\r\ns. In Yoga Vasistha (2.5.14-16), we are told that this applies to Brahma, V=\r\nishnu and Shiva as well.\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;For a moment, let us assume that &quot;freedom fro=\r\nm rebirth&quot; exists. Let us also assume that some beings are &quot;eligible&quot; for s=\r\nuch a moksha. Even in this case, some beings may not choose this path. With=\r\n an extremely light conditioning, they may choose to remain in the world.=\r\n=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt; Is there