lne=\r\nss to the external objective reality is Shakti. Extending this principle to=\r\n the Universe, the purely transcendental non-changing, non-negotiable reali=\r\nty can be called the &quot;atmah&quot; while everything else, semi-transcendental to =\r\nthe objective\n reality all around is Shakti. Thus in short, using scriptura=\r\nl terms, Nirguna Brahman is the state of mind of God, while the Universe(s)=\r\n/various realm(s) is the body of God. Both are irrevocable linked for all p=\r\nractical purposes.&nbsp; Maya is whatever inhibits an individual cell (a hu=\r\nman being or animal or plant or anything) in the body of the God - that is =\r\nUniverse(s) - from realizing the greater picture. &lt;br&gt;\n\n&lt;br&gt;Am I making sen=\r\nse? -:)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Regards&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;yi=\r\nv776828023im&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;yiv776828023MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\r\n=3D&quot;font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;&quot;&gt;awaktam wyaktimAp=\r\nannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n\n&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-SIZE:10pt=\r\n;COLOR:navy;FONT-FAMILY:Verdana;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Times New=\r\n Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam\n ||[7:24]&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div sty=\r\nle=3D&quot;font-family:verdana, helvetica, sans-serif;font-size:10pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div sty=\r\nle=3D&quot;font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt;&quot;&gt;=\r\n\n\n &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;font face=3D&quot;Arial&quot;&gt; &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;yiv=\r\n776828023im&quot;&gt;  &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&g