 infinity, nothing or nobody&nbsp; understands infinity. It is a summation=\r\n of all that we know, all that we can&nbsp; imagine and all that is impossi=\r\nble for us to imagine. It is an incomprehensible force that runs through ev=\r\nerything, from the most loveable to the most despicable , from the most hol=\r\ny to the most unholy, from the greatest saint to the stupidest piece of roc=\r\nk at the bottom of the deepest ocean in the farthest planet in the farthest=\r\n solar system in the farthest universe. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#00=\r\n0000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; =\r\nsize=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;=\r\ndiv align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;Now =\r\nquestion is, can an average human being &quot;know&quot; this mysterious and all perv=\r\nading force? Knowing implies understanding. Clearly no. Then how does one i=\r\nnteract with such a thing? One way is to consider\n everything, and I mean E=\r\nVERYTHING from living to non-living, as a manifestation of that force and t=\r\nhus learn to love the same unconditionally without expecting anything in re=\r\nturn. No wonder such unconditional love is not easy. It needs tremendous ef=\r\nfort to change our own conditioning of the mind, and work on our inherent b=\r\niases and prejudices. That is what the&nbsp; aim of sadhana is, in my view.=\r\n To work on oneself, to make one ready to be able to unconditionally love e=\r\nverything. The greater number of entities one can love unconditionally, tha=\r\nt much little bit closer one can come to interacting with the truly infinit=\r\ne. And those few rare human beings who can love a whole universe unconditio=\r\nnally, are possibly the closest to this supreme and unknowable force. In co=\r\nmmon language, we call them Rishis. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000=\r\n&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D=\r\n&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;I like all forms of\n Deities, for I f=\r\nind something beautiful in everyone of them. And I also like the One behind=\r\n forms, which is so perfectly transcendental that it cannot be comprehended=\r\n ever. It&#39;s like the surface area of the fine tip of a needle, or the gap b=\r\netween the two breaths, or the millionth part of a single hair, or the endl=\r\ness-ness of space, or the bottomless well of stillness in the mind at certa=\r\nin points in meditation. The only thing that stops me from getting a better=\r\n understanding the grandeur of&nbsp; this formless entity are the limitatio=\r\nns of my own mind and body, that I have acquired over millions of births. T=\r\nhat is why Sadhana. To slowly gnaw away at my own mind, to be better able t=\r\no appreciate this endless, nameless entity. G_d. &lt;font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n\n\n\n\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font co=\r\nlor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=\r\n=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;I do not\n believe in Moksha. What =\r\nis Moksha? No rebirth? If the Universe itself gets born over and over and o=\r\nver, if Rama and Krshna come back at every cycle, who am I to demand that I=\r\n should not get born? Infact, when a person proverbially finishes off his/h=\r\ner karmas, they merely go to another plane in this Universe and stay there =\r\nfor eons of time, since time anyway moves very, very slowly in different re=\r\nalms. But then, if this force so wants, it can send back any of the souls f=\r\nrom any of the realms to any of the other realms to serve a certain functio=\r\nn. And if a soul stays in a certain higher realm and in forced to take rebi=\r\nrth again, the seeds of the karmas - which never really die off - are&nbsp;=\r\n watered again by the environment of birth and they sprout into saplings. A=\r\nnd this may go even beyond one cycle of creation. Else why would Krshna and=\r\n Arjuna fight the very same enemies that they had been fighting in the past=\r\n cycle of creation? Mahabharata says so. I\n believe it. &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;font =\r\ncolor=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=\r\n=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; size=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot;=\r\n&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div align=3D&quot;LEFT&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; si=\r\nze=3D&quot;3&quot;&gt;What then is the final aim of all this, spirituality etc? I don&#39;t =\r\nknow. Maybe, to teach us to broaden our perspectives and consequentially le=\r\nssen our attachments to our otherwise mundane lives and its mundane problem=\r\ns. This is like a circular roller-coaster ride we see in local melas. Tight=\r\nen the seat-belts, bring a smile in the heart, be detached and enjoy the sh=\r\now! &lt;font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n\n\n&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=3D&quot;Verdana&quot; =\n(Message over 64 KB, truncated)"}}